column8: Damage to forward lower keel, port side. Slight gouging on rudder
Damage to forward lower keel, port side. Slight gouging on rudder
There appear to be more nicks in the paint forward of the keel.
Unable to clean starboard waterline at midship due to wires in the water and vessel proximity to the dock.
Algae becoming more tenacious near waterline and port bow areas
Rudder was fouled on under dock wires.
Small crack appearing on forward upper rudder
Port waterline has mostly lost anti-fouling effectiveness.
